abstract: Iowa resident Carolyn Miller had long harbored doubts about Joe Biden's candidacy, believing the former vice president was too old and too fumbling to beat President Donald Trump in November's election.
snippet: Iowa resident Carolyn Miller had long harbored doubts about Joe Biden's candidacy, believing the former vice president was too old and too fumbling to beat President Donald Trump in November's election.
lead_paragraph: FORT DODGE, Iowa — Iowa resident Carolyn Miller had long harbored doubts about Joe Biden's candidacy, believing the former vice president was too old and too fumbling to beat President Donald Trump in November's election.
headline_main: How Joe Biden Went From Slumping to Surging in Democratic Presidential Race in Iowa

abstract: Iranian foreign minister Javad Zarif skipped this year's Davos, but Tehran was still a hot topic for many Western and Middle Eastern powers hoping for detente less than three weeks after the United States killed Iran's top general.

lead_paragraph: DAVOS, Switzerland — Iranian foreign minister Javad Zarif skipped this year's Davos, but Tehran was still a hot topic for many Western and Middle Eastern powers hoping for detente less than three weeks after the United States killed Iran's top general.
headline_main: Absent Iran Faces Detente Calls From Worried West and Middle East

abstract: U.S. Democratic presidential hopeful Bernie Sanders' decision to highlight an unofficial endorsement from Joe Rogan drew criticism on Friday due to the comedian's brand of humor that some see as dismissive of issues like equal pay and transgender rights.

abstract: U.S. Vice President Mike Pence, a former Catholic, held an unusually long meeting with Pope Francis on Friday and quipped that he emerged from the encounter feeling like "a hero".
snippet: U.S. Vice President Mike Pence, a former Catholic, held an unusually long meeting with Pope Francis on Friday and quipped that he emerged from the encounter feeling like "a hero".
lead_paragraph: VATICAN CITY — U.S. Vice President Mike Pence, a former Catholic, held an unusually long meeting with Pope Francis on Friday and quipped that he emerged from the encounter feeling like "a hero".
headline_main: Pence to Pope Francis: 'You Have Made Me a Hero'
headline_print_headline: Pence to Pope Francis: 'You Have Made Me a Hero'

abstract: The nonprofit Commission on Presidential Debates has sponsored every general election debate since 1988, but the Trump campaign has raised concerns about its 2020 events.
snippet: The nonprofit Commission on Presidential Debates has sponsored every general election debate since 1988, but the Trump campaign has raised concerns about its 2020 events.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump’s campaign is considering only participating in general election debates if an outside firm serves as the host, and his advisers recently sat down with the nonprofit Commission on Presidential Debates to complain about the debates it hosted in 2016.

abstract: At first, President Donald Trump stated inaccurately that no U.S. troops were injured in the Iranian missile attack against them in Iraq. Then he prematurely minimized those injuries as doctors tried to determine how severe they were.
snippet: At first, President Donald Trump stated inaccurately that no U.S. troops were injured in the Iranian missile attack against them in Iraq. Then he prematurely minimized those injuries as doctors tried to determine how severe they were.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — At first, President Donald Trump stated inaccurately that no U.S. troops were injured in the Iranian missile attack against them in Iraq. Then he prematurely minimized those injuries as doctors tried to determine how severe they were.
headline_main: AP FACT CHECK: Trump's False Assurance About Troops in Iraq
headline_print_headline: AP FACT CHECK: Trump's False Assurance About Troops in Iraq

abstract: Right-wing media have been laying the groundwork for Trump’s acquittal for half a century.
snippet: Right-wing media have been laying the groundwork for Trump’s acquittal for half a century.
lead_paragraph: If you tuned in to Fox News to watch the opening arguments of the impeachment trial on Wednesday night, you were out of luck. Oh, the trial was still technically being broadcast on the network, but it had been reduced to a muted box on the side of the screen, while Sean Hannity assured viewers, “None of this will matter.”

abstract: The Pentagon said on Friday that 34 service members had been diagnosed with traumatic brain injury following missile strikes by Iran on a base in Iraq earlier this month, a number higher than the military had previously announced.
snippet: The Pentagon said on Friday that 34 service members had been diagnosed with traumatic brain injury following missile strikes by Iran on a base in Iraq earlier this month, a number higher than the military had previously announced.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Pentagon said on Friday that 34 service members had been diagnosed with traumatic brain injury following missile strikes by Iran on a base in Iraq earlier this month, a number higher than the military had previously announced.
headline_main: U.S. Says 34 Troops Diagnosed With Traumatic Brain Injury After Iran Strike
headline_print_headline: U.S. Says 34 Troops Diagnosed With Traumatic Brain Injury After Iran Strike

abstract: Executive privilege has no built-in enforcement mechanism that enables a president to involuntarily gag people.
snippet: Executive privilege has no built-in enforcement mechanism that enables a president to involuntarily gag people.
lead_paragraph: Senator Lisa Murkowski, Republican of Alaska, drew attention when she expressed caution about a drawn-out court battle over executive privilege — noting that the House skipped that ordeal. But there is one witness for whom that fear likely does not apply: John R. Bolton, Mr. Trump’s former national security adviser.
headline_main: Fear of court battle over witnesses may not apply to Bolton.
